summary: Captain Marvel's cat and more get new character posters from Marvel Studios
title: Captain Marvel's cat and more get new character posters from Marvel Studios
body:
Captain Marvel’s cat and more get new character posters from Marvel Studios

  

Yes, that is a poster for Captain Marvel’s cat, who will no doubt upstage the entire coming film, Captain Marvel.  The cat, named Chewie in the comic books, apparently had a name change for the film, as shown in its new collar.  Now Goose, presumably after Anthony Edwards’ character in Top Gun, he leads a new round of character posters for the March theatrical release .  It’s the last of the…

summary: Marvel Entertainment Drops New Character Posters for Captain Marvel[[MORE]] Brie Larson stars as Carol Danvers / Captain Marvel....
caption:
Marvel Entertainment Drops New Character Posters for Captain Marvel

Brie Larson stars as Carol Danvers / Captain Marvel.

Samuel L. Jackson as Nick Fury.

Jude Law as the leader of Starforce.

Gemma Chan as Minn-Erva.

Djimon Honsou as Korath.

Annette Bening, whose role is still under wraps.

Lashana Lynch as Maria Rambeau.

Ben Mendelsohn as Talos.

Clark Gregg as Agent Coulson.

Goose. My personal favorite and the real star of the show.

(Images via Marvel Twitter)

summary: Ben Wheatley's 'Rebecca' Taps 'Darkest Hour'/'Sherlock Holmes’ Production Designer Sarah Greenwood - GWW
body:
Armie’s next film, Rebecca, is ramping up nicely to start shooting in May. The announced production designer is tops.

But what I really want to know is who will play Mrs Danvers, the Housekeeper. The director hinted at an exciting name. Who could it be? Ideas?

I’d love Nicole, Rosamund, Brie or Rachel Weisz.

Ben Wheatley’s ‘Rebecca’ Taps 'Darkest Hour’/'Sherlock Holmes’ Production Designer Sarah Greenwood - GWW

I Marvel Studios hanno rilasciato oggi i 10 characters poster dedicati a Captain Marvel, il cinecomic di prossima uscita, parte del Marvel Cinematic Universe.

Tra i protagonisti dei poster: la stessa Captain Marvel (Brie Larson), Nick Fury (Samuel L. Jackson), l’Agente Coulson (Clark Gregg), e Mar-Vell (Jude Law).
